column5: Yup around 8"-9", went back to that same spot with my son yesterday and he measured it at 13". We had a cold snap since tuesday when I was there, you could here the ice booming in the video from Tuesday, made four inches in as many days, crazy.Ice measure videohttps://youtu.be/WoBxWhhFVug
Ok Chewbacca,after having patience for a long time it starts to run thin

True enough, I think we are all feeling the pressure in many different ways but the virus cares little about how we all feel unfortunately. I count myself lucky to live in a sparsely populated area of the world but that does not mean I or the community is immune, all I can do is mask up and wash my hands....alot, its not to hard for me to do that, and social distancing has made no real difference to me anyway...lol...I prefer it that way most of the time!

Hi all, Been a while, crazy 12 months eh? been fishing lots up here, just lost my mojo to make videos. Finally sat down yesterday and pieced a quickie together to share with y'all, no walleye, but some nice pike and trout all visible right under my boots, cool to watch...enjoy, hope to see you guys back as soon as its safe for all of us.VIDEOhttps://youtu.be/UjXrqLeYvtw
Thanks for the video. Great to see you gain! I was getting concerned...
Thanks for video. Makes me miss the place more. Take care.
Nice! We are just getting walkable ice now.
Good times and thanks for sharing

Its been a crazy mild winter here so far, I don't think we have more than 18" anywhere yet up here, if it stays mild and we should be in the boats by end of March, practically unheard of!
